---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Parallax Playbook"
  description="What Parallax Playbook is: one carefully researched post a day on quantum computing, consciousness, and mathematics — and the threads between them."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 sm:px-8 pt-20 pb-24">
    <p class="micro mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight mb-10">A parallax on the edge of what's known.</h1>

    <div class="post-body">
      <p>
        Parallax is the shift in how a thing looks when you move your point of view.
        Hold up a finger, close one eye, then the other — it jumps. The object didn't
        move; you did. That small shift is also how we measure the distance to stars.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is built on the bet that three fields — <strong>quantum computing</strong>,
        <strong>consciousness</strong>, and <strong>mathematics</strong> — are each circling the
        same deep questions from different angles, and that the interesting things live
        in the parallax between them: what shifts, and what stays fixed, as you move from
        one viewpoint to the next.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <p>
        One post a day. Each one takes a genuinely new finding, idea, or revelation from
        these fields, researches it properly, and rewrites it as something a curious person
        can read in a few minutes — without dumbing it down. No hype, no jargon for its
        own sake, no twenty-tab rabbit hole required. Just the clearest version of the
        idea I can manage, and an honest sense of why it matters.
      </p>

      <h2>The shape of it</h2>
      <p>
        Sleek, dark, quiet. Built to be read, not to shout. New posts land in
        <a href="/posts">the feed</a>, and you can follow along by
        <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>.
      </p>

      <p>Questions, corrections, or a finding I should cover? <a href="mailto:hello@parallaxplaybook.com">hello@parallaxplaybook.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
